Hands down the best restaurant in the neighborhood if you have kids. We have three and every time we went, which was often, my wife and I were able to eat knowing that our kids would eat well and have fun. What separates JPan from other restaurants is the staff. They are absolutely wonderful and truly love kids. It's almost like a small community where every kids that goes to the restaurant becomes best friends with the staff. Anyway, after moving to NJ, we have yet to find anything close to our JPan family, and we probably never will. I guess that means we'll just have to go back to visit Brooklyn more often. Thanks for such wonderful experiences over these past 10 years.

I ordered from this place once and was going to order from here again, but changed my mind. The first time they were super rude, took forever with my food, and from the restaurant to my apartment RIGHT NEXT DOOR my food was cold. Does not make any sense. Today I had an incident with them. A little backstory, I babysit and had to pick up a kid early from school, he didnt have lunch so I bought him a hot dog from the cart outside of the Carroll Street F/G station. I gave a $20 and received $16 in change which I just threw in my bag. Now I go to this sushi place and order a house chicken roll for me and miso soup for the kid I'm babysitting. It comes out to $10.62. I give $11 and the lady was like I'm not taking this. She was referring to the $10. She didnt tell me what was wrong and I was confused and finally she was like it's not real. I'm like okay so I'm about to pull about my debit card and shes just staring at me looking very judgmental  so I was like forget it. The $10 did turn out to be fake, I walked right to the TD bank on the corner and gave it to them. I never have any issues with sushi places and I've been to a lot. All I know is that I will not be going back even if it is right next door to where I babysit. I will take my money elsewhere.
